      "rationale": "Single turbulence model (SST k-omega) and single hemolysis exponent set used; no multi-model comparison or Bayesian averaging performed. Model-form uncertainty not characterised. Factor flagged as not-assessed at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (fluid properties, hemolysis coefficients, turbulence model constants) characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation performed to quantify input uncertainty contribution to NIH.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed on five input parameters (viscosity, density, hemolysis power-law coefficient C and exponent alpha, inlet velocity profile); hemolysis model constants drawn from literature distributions. However, material property temperature dependence not included in distributions, and impeller surface roughness treated as deterministic. Achieved level 2 against required level 4.",
      "note": "Primary experimental dataset (fda-pump-hemolysis-exp-2025q4, dataVintage 2025-10-18) used to calibrate hemolysis power-law input distributions predates the modelRevisionDate of 2025-11-10T09:00:00Z. The geometry revision altering impeller trailing-edge curvature was characterised by the assessment team as not material to bulk hemolysis predictions; no re-calibration of input distributions against post-revision geometry was performed."
